The paper deals with video understanding and proposes a new model for actor-action semantic segmentation. This problem is closely related to computer vision (cs.CV) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) as it involves recognizing and understanding actions and actors in videos. The proposed model also involves a hierarchical supervoxel decomposition, which is a technique commonly used in machine learning and computer vision (cs.LG). The paper also mentions experimental results on a large-scale video dataset, which suggests that it may fall under the multimedia (cs.MM) category. Finally, the model involves dynamic and continuous exchange of information, which is a characteristic of robotics (cs.RO) research.
